This is my configuration for linux fedora based on my own experience and various tutorials.


RPM Fusion repository: https://rpmfusion.org/Configuration
sudo dnf install https://mirrors.rpmfusion.org/free/fedora/rpmfusion-free-release-$(rpm -E %fedora).noarch.rpm https://mirrors.rpmfusion.org/nonfree/fedora/rpmfusion-nonfree-release-$(rpm -E %fedora).noarch.rpm

AppStream metadata
sudo dnf groupupdate core

Multimedia and codecs
sudo dnf groupupdate multimedia --setop="install_weak_deps=False" --exclude=PackageKit-gstreamer-plugin
sudo dnf groupupdate sound-and-video
sudo dnf install gstreamer1-plugins-* ffmpeg vlc

Tainted repos
sudo dnf install rpmfusion-free-release-tainted
sudo dnf install libdvdcss


Flatpak setup: https://flatpak.org/setup/Fedora/
sudo flatpak remote-add --if-not-exists flathub https://flathub.org/repo/flathub.flatpakrepo


Install VAAPI - Intel GPU
lspci | grep VGA
sudo dnf install libva libva-intel-driver libva-vdpau-driver libva-utils libva-intel-hybrid-driver


Thermald (Intel Thermal Daemon): https://github.com/intel/thermal_daemon 
sudo dnf groupinstall "Development Tools" "C Development Tools and Libraries"
sudo yum install automake gcc gcc-c++ glib-devel libxml2-devel dbus-glib-devel autoconf-archive gtk-doc upower-devel xz-devel libevdev-devel

Download latest release: https://github.com/intel/thermal_daemon/tags
./autogen.sh prefix=/
make
sudo make install

1. Start service: sudo systemctl start thermald.service
2. Get Status: sudo systemctl status thermald.service
3. Stop service: sudo systemctl stop thermald.service
4. Terminate using DBUS I/F: sudo test/test_pref.sh  (and select "TERMINATE" choice)
5. Enable Service: sudo systemctl enable thermald
6. Start service: sudo systemctl start thermald.service


Power profiles daemon: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/hadess/power-profiles-daemon
sudo dnf install power-profiles-daemon

Powertop: https://01.org/powertop/overview
sudo dnf install powertop

Google Chrome: https://www.google.com/linuxrepositories/
wget https://dl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub
sudo rpm --import linux_signing_key.pub
rpm -qi gpg-pubkey-7fac5991-*


Chromium-freeworld - VAAPI Support: https://major.io/2019/10/20/install-chromium-with-vaapi-on-fedora-30/
sudo dnf -y install chromium-freeworld
Enable DRM:
sudo cp /opt/google/chrome/libwidevinecdm.so /usr/lib64/chromium-freeworld/


Steam:
sudo dnf install steam libtxc_dxtn.i686 ibtxc_dxtn.x86_64


GRUB Setup:
GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX="rhgb quiet acpi_osi=Linux pcie_aspm=force drm.vblankoffdelay=1 zswap.enabled=1 zswap.compressor=lz4 i915.enable_guc=2 scsi_mod.use_blk_mq=1 intel_iommu=on intel_pstate=passive mitigations=off"

sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/efi/EFI/fedora/grub.cfg


TRIM Support
sudo systemctl enable fstrim.timer
sudo systemctl start fstrim.timer
sudo fstrim -v /



